<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angels' Hill Injures Rib Cage  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Angels pitcher Ken Hill left Tuesday
night's game against Oakland in the third inning after straining a
muscle in the right side of his rib cage.
</P>
<P>
   Hill, who threw 67 pitches, sustained the injury while throwing
a fastball to Miguel Tejada with one out and a man on first. After
finishing his follow-through, Hill sank to his knees and doubled
over in pain as the Angels training staff went to his aid.
</P>
<P>
   Hill, 34, is 3-3 with a 7.47 ERA in eight starts. The
right-hander was on the disabled list twice last season, once
because of inflammation in his pitching elbow.
</P>
<P>
   The Angels already have starters Jason Dickson and Tim Belcher
on the disabled list. Dickson, who had a strained hip flexor, is
eligible to come off the DL on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   But Belcher isn't expected to come back until June -- at the
earliest -- because of inflammation in his right elbow.
</P>
</TEXT>
