<HEADLINE> 14 Rescued When Dive Boat Sinks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KEY WEST, Fla. (AP) -- Eleven passengers and three crew members
were rescued Tuesday when a dive boat sank two miles off shore --
the second time in eight months the craft sank.
</P>
<P>
   The crew of the 48-foot boat ''Manta'' issued a mayday call at
about 12:30 p.m. EDT saying that the stern was awash and that they
were sinking quickly, Coast Guard officials said.
</P>
<P>
   A second dive boat responded and pulled the crew and passengers
to safety. A Coast Guard ship also went to the scene.
</P>
<P>
   Suki York, marketing director for the Manta's owner, Southpoint
Divers, said the boat also sank in September. It was salvaged and
restored.
</P>
<P>
   The Manta was again salvaged Tuesday and it will be inspected to
determine why it sank, York said.
</P>
</TEXT>
