<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-10 07:14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Michigan, Illinois winners in $350 million Big Game drawing  </HEADLINE>
By A.J. DICKERSON, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   UTICA, Mich. (AP) -- Michigan and Illinois have winners in the
$350 million Big Game lottery, spokeswomen for the states' lottery
bureaus said today.
</P>
<P>
   A ticket matching the numbers drawn Tuesday night in the
multistate lottery was sold at Mr. K's Party Shoppe in suburban
Detroit, Michigan Lottery spokeswoman Sarah Lapshan said from
Lansing.
</P>
<P>
   ''Thank God,'' she said, laughing.
</P>
<P>
   A winning ticket also was sold somewhere in Illinois, said
Illinois Lottery spokeswoman Anne Plohr-Rayhill. She said she did
not know where it was sold.
</P>
<P>
   Mr. K's Party Shoppe is in Macomb County's Shelby Township near
Utica, about 20 miles north of Detroit. Located in a small strip
mall with two other businesses, it was closed at 5 a.m. today, but
television trucks and other news vehicles already crowded the
rain-dampened parking lot.
</P>
<P>
   A switched-off neon sign in the window said ''Lottery.''
</P>
<P>
   Lapshan said she did not yet know if any other winning tickets
were sold in other states. There was only one winning ticket sold
in Michigan, she said.
</P>
<P>
   ''All we can confirm is a winning ticket in Michigan at this
time,'' Lapshan said.
</P>
<P>
   Tickets for the Big Game are sold in Georgia, Illinois,
Maryland, Massachusetts, Michigan, New Jersey and Virginia.
</P>
<P>
   New Jersey Lottery officials said no winning tickets were sold
there. Maryland authorities also reported no winning tickets.
</P>
<P>
   Results from the other states hadn't been released by early
today.
</P>
<P>
   No one answered the telephone at Mr. K's Party Shoppe early
today.
</P>
<P>
   The winning numbers were one, two, 12, 33 and 37, and the Big
Money Ball number was four. To win, a ticket had to match the five
numbers and the Big Money Ball.
</P>
<P>
   After taxes, based on federal and Georgia state taxes, the
payout on a single winning ticket is either $8.9 million a year for
26 years, or a one-time payment of $114 million. The state tax
varies among the seven states.
</P>
<P>
   The $350 million jackpot tops the previous American record for a
lottery. That was a $295.7 million Powerball jackpot split by 13
machinists in Westerville, Ohio, two years ago.
</P>
<P>
   The world lottery record is $1.2 billion, set in December by
Spain's El Gordo lottery, or the Fat One. But that game spreads
itself thin by awarding thousands of prizes.
</P>
<P>
   The odds that a $1 Big Game ticket will have all five winning
numbers and the matching Big Money Ball are one in more than 76
million.
</P>
<P>
   Robert Holland, a bartender at the East Atlanta Restaurant and
Lounge in Georgia, said he knew the odds were stacked against him
when he bought his ticket. The odds of having all five winning
numbers and the Big Money Ball were one in more than 76 million.
</P>
<P>
   ''At least I only lost a dollar,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Others weren't as lucky. Some players plopped down hundreds of
dollars in the hopes of becoming instant millionaires. Others
pooled their money with coworkers and friends to buy more chances.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   Big Game: http://www.theofficialbiggame.com
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
