<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Open Lower  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices were lower in early trading on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones Industrial Average was down 44 points in the early
going. Losing issues on the New York Stock Exchange held a 7-4 lead
over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index was off 60 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index was down 7 points.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts predict there could be some bargain-hunting on the
market.
</P>
<P>
   With the Nasdaq down sharply the past two days, and losing more
ground in early trading, some investors might see this as a buying
situation.
</P>
<P>
   At the same time, market-watchers expect little overall
direction for the market for the next several days.
</P>
<P>
   Many investors are standing by for next week's Federal Reserve
meeting, in which the central bank is widely expected to raise
interest rates once again to calm the economy.
</P>
