the numbers right in the record $366 million Big Game lottery. There was no
immediate word on who the winning people were. Frenzied buying in seven states
had led to the jumbo jackpot. One of the two tickets was sold at Mr. K's Party
Shoppe near Utica, 20 miles north of Detroit. The other winning ticket was sold
at Sweeney's Citgo in the northwestern Chicago suburb of Lake Zurich, Ill. The
winning numbers drawn last night in Atlanta were 1, 2, 12, 33, 37 and Big Money
Ball 4.
