<P>
	   WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) -- The second of two college sweethearts from Wyckoff,
N.J., who pleaded guilty to killing their newborn son in a motel room left
prison today, eight months early. Amy Grossberg was sentenced in July 1998 to 2
1/2 years for manslaughter. She was released early for time served before her
sentencing and for good behavior. Grossberg and Brian Peterson were 18-year-old
college freshmen on Nov. 12, 1996, when they went to a motel room near the
University of Delaware campus and she gave birth to his son. The baby was later
found wrapped in plastic in a trash bin in the motel parking lot. Peterson
pleaded guilty in March 1998 and was given a two-year sentence after he agreed
to testify against Grossberg. He left prison on Jan. 4 after 18 months.
</P>
