<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spacey Offers Lesson on DeVito  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Kevin Spacey applied hardball marketing
tactics to land Danny DeVito as co-star in his new movie about
salesmen, ''The Big Kahuna.''
</P>
<P>
   ''I lied to him, actually,'' Spacey said, describing the
scramble to replace an actor initially cast opposite Spacey and
Peter Facinelli, who play a three-man sales team at a convention.
</P>
<P>
   Spacey called DeVito on a Friday early last year for a shoot
that was beginning the next week. ''I told him the role had been
specifically written for him, and he was really impressed. He said,
'Wow, that doesn't happen all that often.'''
</P>
<P>
   DeVito asked when production would start, figuring ''I was going
to say next year some time,'' Spacey said. ''I told him, actually,
funnily enough, we're going to begin shooting on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ''He said, 'Wait a minute, let me just back up a sec, Kev. A
role that was specifically written for me, you're beginning to
shoot on Tuesday, and this is the first call I'm getting?'
</P>
<P>
   ''I said, 'Well, it should have been written for you is what I
meant to say.' He said, 'Great, the next time I have a part for
somebody lying and conniving, I'm going to give you a call.'
</P>
<P>
   ''But he read the material that night, he fell madly in love
with it, he was on a plane two days later and filming with us on
Tuesday.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-05-10-00 1204 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
