<HEADLINE> Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   In the birthday spotlight:
</P>
<P>
   Hundreds of people showed up when English rock singer Joe Cocker
had a yard sale at his mansion in Crawford, Colo., to raise money
for charity. Among the items sold: baby clothes, pillowcases and a
toilet seat. Cocker, who was born on May 20, 1944, also sold a
Fender guitar and a Woodstock '94 autographed dressing room sign.
Proceeds went to the Cocker Kids Foundation.
</P>
<P>
   ''Star Wars: Episode 1 -- The Phantom Menace'' thrust the
earnings of the film series' creator George Lucas into the
stratosphere, putting him on top of Forbes magazine's list of
celebrity earnings in 1999. Lucas earned $400 million, putting him
far ahead of Oprah Winfrey, whose talk show and other ventures
earned $150 million. Lucas was born on May 14, 1944.
</P>
<P>
   When Dennis Hopper was asked why he agreed to star in ''Jason
and the Argonauts,'' NBC's adaptation of the famed saga from Greek
mythology, he replied: ''Probably for the money.'' Then he added,
''This is classic stuff and it is produced and cast to reflect
that. Many of the actors are English or Irish with training in
Shakespeare.'' Hopper was born on May 17, 1936.
</P>
<P>
   Celebrity birthdays May 14-20:
</P>
<P>
   May 14: Movie producer George Lucas is 56. Director Robert
Zemeckis is 48. Actor Tim Roth is 39. Singer Ian Astbury of the
Cult is 38. Musician Mike Inez of Alice in Chains is 34. Actress
Cate Blanchett is 31. Singer Danny Wood of New Kids on the Block is
31. Singer Natalie Appleton of All Saints is 27. Singer Shanice is
27.
</P>
<P>
   May 15: Singer Trini Lopez is 63. Actress-singer Lainie Kazan is
60. Country singer K.T. Oslin is 58. Singer-songwriter Brian Eno is
52. Actor Chazz Palminteri is 49. Singer-rapper Prince Be with PM
Dawn is 30. Actor David Charvet (''Melrose Place'') is 28.
</P>
<P>
   May 16: Actor Pierce Brosnan is 47. Actress Debra Winger is 45.
Actress Mare Winningham is 41. Singer Janet Jackson is 34. Actress
Tracey Gold is 31. Actor David Boreanaz (''Angel'') is 29. Actress
Tori Spelling is 27.
</P>
<P>
   May 17: Actor Dennis Hopper is 64. Singer Taj Mahal is 58. Actor
Bill Paxton (''U-571'') is 45. Actor-comedian Bob Saget is 44.
Musician O'Dell of Mint Condition is 35. Singer-musician Trent
Reznor of Nine Inch Nails is 35. Singer Jordan Knight of New Kids
on the Block is 30. Singer Darnell Van Rensalier of Shai is 30.
Singer Kandi Burruss of Xscape is 24.
</P>
<P>
   May 18: Singer Perry Como is 88. Actor Bill Macy is 78. Actor
Dwayne Hickman (''The Many Loves of Dobie Gillis'') is 66. Musician
Rick Wakeman of Yes is 51. Country singer George Strait is 48.
Singer-musician Page Hamilton of Helmet is 40. Singer-actress
Martika (''Wiseguy'') is 31. Rapper Special Ed is 26. Singer Darryl
Allen of Mista is 20.
</P>
<P>
   May 19: TV personality David Hartman is 65. Musician Phil Rudd
of AC/DC is 54. Singer-musician Dusty Hill of ZZ Top is 51. Singer
Joey Ramone of the Ramones is 48. Singer Jenny Berggren of Ace of
Base is 28. Actor Eric Lloyd (''Jesse'') is 14.
</P>
<P>
   May 20: Singer Joe Cocker is 56. Singer-actress Cher is 54.
Actor Dave Thomas is 51. Actor Bronson Pinchot is 41. Actor Tony
Goldwyn is 40. Singer Susan Cowsill of the Cowsills is 40. Singer
Nick Heyward of Haircut 100 is 39. Actress Mindy Cohn (''Facts of
Life'') is 34. Musician Tom Gorman of Belly is 34. Rapper Busta
Rhymes is 28.
</P>
</TEXT>
