<HEADLINE> AP Names Chicago Asst. Bureau Chief  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Daniel C. Sewell, an editor with The Cincinnati
Enquirer and a veteran Associated Press newsman, is returning to
the AP as assistant chief of bureau in Chicago.
</P>
<P>
   The appointment was announced Wednesday by Chief of Bureau James
Reindl.
</P>
<P>
   Sewell worked for the news cooperative for 22 years before
taking a job with the Enquirer last year directing coverage of
Cincinnati's northern suburbs.
</P>
<P>
   During his AP tenure, Sewell served as Florida news editor,
based in Miami, and Caribbean news editor, based in San Juan,
Puerto Rico. He also was a sports writer and editor, a business
editor and a correspondent-at-large in Florida and later Georgia.
Sewell also served as a regional writer for the Southeast, based in
Atlanta. He began his AP career in Cincinnati in 1977 and moved to
Buffalo later that year.
</P>
<P>
   Sewell, 45, replaces Sarah Nordgren, who has become deputy
director of state news for the AP. A native of Middletown, Ohio,
Sewell earned a bachelor's degree at Ohio University.
</P>
</TEXT>
