<HEADLINE> News Desks Flooded at Treasury  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Pipes burst and flooded out some news
organizations at the Treasury Department, forcing the agency to
close its press room Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
   The flood started around 2:15 p.m. EDT when ceiling pipes
suddenly began spewing a rust-colored liquid.
</P>
<P>
   News desks belonging to The Associated Press, Reuters, Dow
Jones, AFX News and Bridge News were in the area hardest hit by the
flooding. Some news organizations' computers and other equipment
were damaged.
</P>
<P>
   Treasury spokeswoman Michelle Smith ordered the room closed
shortly after the flood began. The cause of the pipe rupture was
not immediately determined. The room was expected to be reopened on
Thursday.
</P>
