<HEADLINE> Gun Found in Preschooler's Bag  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BAKER, Fla. (AP) -- A school bus driver found a loaded gun in the
book bag of a 5-year-old pupil, who said he was copying someone he
had seen on television, police said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   ''There's no indication he had any intention of harming anyone
or threatening anyone,'' Okaloosa County sheriff's spokesman Rick
Hord said.
</P>
<P>
   A third-grader spotted the small, .380 semiautomatic handgun in
the pre-kindergartener's book bag Tuesday as they rode the bus home
from the all-ages Baker School.
</P>
<P>
   The older child reported the gun to the driver.
</P>
<P>
   No action will be taken against the 5-year-old, who had found
the gun in a drawer at home. Prosecutors are considering whether to
charge his parents with a misdemeanor for failing to store the
weapon properly, Hord said.
</P>
<P>
   The boy told a school resource officer he had seen someone carry
a gun in a book bag on television and thought it was ''cool.''
