<HEADLINE> Expos Closer Urbina To Have MRI  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MONTREAL (AP) -- Montreal Expos closer Ugueth Urbina was
unavailable for Wednesday night's game against the Philadelphia
Phillies after feeling pain in his right elbow while warming up the
previous night.
</P>
<P>
   Urbina, last year's NL saves leader with 41, told team officials
about the pain following the Expos' 3-2 win Tuesday night. X-rays
of the elbow were taken on Wednesday and an MRI will be performed
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Urbina, 26, had bone chips removed from his right elbow in
December 1996 after experiencing pain while pitching in his native
Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
   He struck out the side while recording his eighth save in his
last outing, Sunday at Milwaukee.
</P>
<P>
   Graeme Lloyd, signed as a free agent be to Montreal's set man,
hasn't pitched this season. He had arthroscopic surgery on his left
shoulder May 4 and won't return for at least three months.
</P>
<P>
   Scott Strickland, the Expos' current setup man, is on the
disabled list because of right shoulder tendinitis.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
