<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feds Seek Injunction Vs. Goya Foods  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- The National Labor Relations Board filed for an
injunction Wednesday against Goya Foods, charging the company
unfairly limited labor organizing efforts at its Miami distribution
center.
</P>
<P>
   The request is an outgrowth of a separate NLRB complaint
awaiting trial next month which charges the nation's largest
Hispanic-owned food company with more than 40 unfair labor
practices.
</P>
<P>
   A call Wednesday to Goya's Miami office seeking comment was not
immediately returned.
</P>
<P>
   The federal agency is seeking reinstatement of four workers
fired last summer over their reports of rat droppings in a Goya
warehouse and a rat's nest in a Goya carton at a supermarket.
</P>
<P>
   Monica Russo, state director of the union Unite, called the
injunction request ''a scathing indictment of the outrageous
conduct that Goya Foods has attempted to deny and cover up.''
</P>
<P>
   The union won a representation election in 1998 -- but still has
no contract for warehouse workers, drivers and salesmen. As part of
its petition, the NLRB wants a federal judge to order Goya to
resume good-faith bargaining.
</P>
<P>
   The NLRB charged Goya has illegally barred employees from
wearing union paraphernalia at work and threatened them ''with
underemployment if they support the union.''
</P>
<P>
   Federal, state and Miami-Dade County lawmakers also have called
for the reinstatement of the fired workers.
</P>
<P>
   After their complaints, Florida temporarily shut down Goya's
bean packaging operation because it found evidence of rodent
droppings and unsanitary equipment. The state gave the warehouse
its lowest overall rating of ''poor.''
</P>
<P>
   Last September, the U.S. Occupational Safety and Health
Administration issued a $14,000 penalty against Goya for eight
serious violations.
</P>
<P>
   The family owned company based in Secaucus, N.J., sells more
than 1,000 products under the Goya, Kirby, Nacelle and Diana
brands.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
